        <style>
            body    {background-color:black; font-size:150%; border: 2px solid white}

            h1      {color:white; font-family: garamond; text-align:center;}
            h2      {color:white; font-family: garamond; padding: 20px;}
            p       {color:white; font-family: garamond; padding: 30px; margin: 50px; border: 2px solid white}

            address {color:white; font-family: garamond; padding: 10px; font-size:80%}
        </style>
    </head>

    <body>
        <h1>HTML CSS</h1>

        <hr>

        <h2>HTML Styles - Internal CSS</h2>
        <p>
            CSS Stands for <b>Cascading Style Sheets</b>.<br>
        </p>
        <p>
            An Internal CSS is used to define a style for a single HTML Page.
        </p>

        <h2>
            CSS Colors, Fonts and Sizes
        </h2>
        <p>
            The <b>CSS Colour</b> property defines the Colour of the Text Element.<br>
            The <b>CSS Font</b> property defines the Font Style of the Text Element.<br>
            The <b>CSS Size</b> property defines the Size of the Text Element.
        </p>

        <h2>
            CSS Border
        </h2>
        <p>
            The <b>CSS Border</b> property defines a border around the Text Element.
        </p>

        <h2>
            CSS Padding
        </h2>
        <p>
            The <b>CSS Padding</b> property defines a padding around between the margin and the border.
        </p>

        <h2>
            CSS Margin
        </h2>
        <p>
            The <b> CSS Margin</b> property defines a margin outside the border.
        </p>

        <hr>

